
Overview of noun isolation

The noun isolation has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) isolation -- (a state of separation between persons or groups)
2. (1) isolation -- (a feeling of being disliked and alone)
3. (1) isolation, closing off -- (the act of isolating something; setting something apart from others)
4. isolation -- ((psychiatry) a defense mechanism in which memory of an unacceptable act or impulse is separated from the emotion originally associated with it)
5. isolation -- (a country's withdrawal from international politics; "he opposed a policy of American isolation")
